Stephanie Nadolny https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stephanie_Nadolny 0 Stephanie Ann Nadolny (born May 19, 1972) is an American voice actress and singer known for her voice role as the child version of Goku, the protagonist of the Dragon Ball anime series and the child version of Goku's son, Gohan, in Dragon Ball Z. She reprised both roles in several Dragon Ball related video games and media. In 2013, she voiced her first non-anime role as KO in the pilot of the Cartoon Network Studios original program Lakewood Plaza Turbo and its television adaptation, OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes from 2017-2018.
